@flexiarg vsatelier/federated-cosmoses
@title Federated Cosmoses
@audience platform architects, network organisers, digital library architects
@tone analytic
@style design-pattern
@sigils [🌐/宇]
@references [vsatlatarium/anthology-as-filter vsatlas/open-progression-ecosystem vsatlas/open-infrastructure-expert-practice]

! conclusion:
  Multiple independent constellations should be able to federate — each
  visible as a node in a meta-level view — so that separate organisations,
  programmes, or communities can maintain sovereignty while discovering
  cross-boundary patterns.

  + context: You are designing for a network of organisations that each run their own story worlds but want selective interoperability. This does not apply to single-organisation deployments with no external connections.
  + IF:
    Several organisations each maintain their own VSAT/VSATLAS
    installations — a university, a community group, an NGO, a
    farming cooperative.

  + HOWEVER:
    Isolated installations cannot reveal patterns that span organisational
    boundaries. A migrant story in one installation and a policy story in
    another may describe the same systemic failure, but neither community
    sees the connection.

  + THEN:
    Define a federation protocol: each installation publishes a summary
    (story count, cluster structure, link types, anthology list) without
    exposing raw content. A meta-constellation renders each installation
    as a single node — click to enter that cosmos. Opt-in cross-boundary
    links allow specific stories to bridge cosmoses when both parties
    consent.

  + BECAUSE:
    Federation preserves sovereignty (each community owns its data and
    governance) while enabling the emergent patterns that only appear
    at scale. This is the digital-library equivalent of inter-library
    loan: you do not merge the libraries; you create a protocol for
    sharing what each is willing to share.

  + STATUS:
    status[sketch]

  + NEXT-STEPS:
    next[Define the minimal federation summary schema (what an installation publishes about itself).]
    next[Prototype the meta-constellation view with two synthetic installations.]
    next[Design the consent workflow for cross-boundary linking (both stewards must approve).]
    next[Evaluate whether existing protocols (ActivityPub, Solid, IIIF) could carry the federation data.]
